.TH "__napi_build_skb" 9 "__napi_build_skb" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__napi_build_skb \- build a network buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sk_buff *" __napi_build_skb
.BI "(void *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int frag_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "data" 12
data buffer provided by caller
.IP "frag_size" 12
size of data, or 0 if head was kmalloced
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Version of \fB__build_skb\fP that uses NAPI percpu caches to obtain
skbuff_head instead of inplace allocation.

Returns a new \fIsk_buff\fP on success, NULL on allocation failure.
